<article>
    <h1>Smart na&#xAD;tion and dig&#xAD;i&#xAD;tal econ&#xAD;omy</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201212/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-12"><time>2020-12-12</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• Ear­lier re­search ef­forts had boosted the coun­try ’s ex­per­tise in var­i­ous tech­nolo­gies, such as ar­ti­fi­cial in­tel­li­gence and cy­ber se­cu­rity.</p>
    <p>• Sin­ga­pore now wants to take them a step fur­ther, by lever­ag­ing th­ese tech­nolo­gies to drive its smart na­tion am­bi­tion.</p>
    <p>Ex­am­ple: Strate­gic Cen­tre for Re­search in Pri­vacy-Pre­serv­ing Tech­nolo­gies and Sys­tems (Scripts)</p>
    <p>• Scripts has con­ducted re­search in var­i­ous types of pri­vacy-pre­serv­ing tech­nolo­gies to over­come pri­vacy con­cerns faced with data shar­ing.</p>
    <p>• Such tech­nolo­gies could be ap­plied to in­dus­tries look­ing to use data-shar­ing an­a­lyt­ics but were pre­vi­ously dis­cour­aged due to data pro­tec­tion obli­ga­tions or pri­vacy con­cerns.</p>
    <p>• One ex­am­ple of this is a search en­cryp­tion tech­nol­ogy: This al­lows users to per­form a key­word search through a data­base of en­crypted doc­u­ments; how­ever, it would still re­quire a pass­word to open the file when it’s down­loaded. Con­ven­tional search en­gines can­not yield re­sults from a pro­tected doc­u­ment as it can­not be opened.</p>
    <p>We will con­tinue to drive re­search ex­cel­lence in RIE2025, fo­cus­ing on po­ten­tially game-chang­ing ar­eas of tech­nol­ogy... but to de­velop glob­ally rel­e­vant, lead­ing dig­i­tal so­lu­tions, we must do more, es­pe­cially to strengthen the trans­la­tion of re­search find­ings into tan­gi­ble prod­ucts and ser­vices that meet the needs of so­ci­eties and economies.</p>
    <p>MIN­IS­TER FOR COM­MU­NI­CA­TIONS AND IN­FOR­MA­TION S. ISWARAN</p>

